.bashrcd
========
This is the directory to my .bashrc file

Install
-------

Simply download the folder to your $HOME and add the following lines to your $HOME/.bashrc file:

if [ -d $HOME/.bashrc.d ]; then
    for x in $HOME/.bashrc.d/* ; do
        test -f "$x" || continue
        test -x "$x" || continue
        . "$x"
    done
fi

This is a modified version of something described by chisel at http://blogs.perl.org/users/chisel/2011/08/managing-my-shell-setup.html
